n## Configuration System\\n\\nConfiguration supports:\\n- Provider-specific API keys via environment variables\\n- Agent-level settings (model selection, max tokens)\\n- LSP configuration per language\\n- Custom shell path and arguments\\n- \\\"Auto compact feature\\\" for context window management (auto-summarizes conversations at 95% capacity)\\n\\n## Storage & Sessions\\n\\n- Persistent SQLite-based storage for conversations\\n- Session management with file change tracking\\n- Configurable data directory\\n\\n**Note:** The documentation excerpt doesn't detail the internal plugin API, session event schemas, or transcript format specifications—these implementation details aren't covered in the provided content.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"9acd3d39-40c7-40a2-8427-8430062b8c60\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T12:17:26.769Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"bytes\":505183,\"code\":200,\"codeText\":\"OK\",\"result\":\"# OpenCode Architecture & Integration Documentation\\n\\nBased on the provided web content, here's what I found about OpenCode's technical architecture:\\n\\n## Core Architecture\\n\\nOpenCode is a **Go-based CLI application** built with:\\n- **Bubble Tea** for the Terminal User Interface (TUI)\\n- **SQLite database** for persistent storage of conversations and sessions\\n- **Language Server Protocol (LSP)** support for code intelligence\\n\\n## AI Provider Support\\n\\nThe system integrates with multiple AI providers through a modular provider system:\\n- OpenAI (GPT-4.1, GPT-4.5, GPT-4o, O1/O3 families)\\n- Anthropic Claude (3.5/3.7 Sonnet, 4 variants)\\n- Google Gemini (2.5, 2.0 Flash)\\n- GitHub Copilot\\n- AWS Bedrock\\n- Groq\\n- Azure OpenAI\\n- Google Cloud VertexAI\\n- OpenRouter\\n\\n## Tool Integration System\\n\\nThe AI assistant has access to tools enabling:\\n- Command execution capabilities\\n- File searching functionality\\n- Code modification abilities\\n- \\\"Tool integration\\\" for external capabilities\\n\\nThe configuration supports **MCP (Model Context Protocol) Servers** with stdio-type connections, allowing external tool integration through standardized interfaces.\\n\\n## Configuration System\\n\\nConfiguration supports:\\n- Provider-specific API keys via environment variables\\n- Agent-level settings (model selection, max tokens)\\n- LSP configuration per language\\n- Custom shell path and arguments\\n- \\\"Auto compact feature\\\" for context window management (auto-summarizes conversations at 95% capacity)\\n\\n## Storage & Sessions\\n\\n- Persistent SQLite-based storage for conversations\\n- Session management with file change tracking\\n- Configurable data directory\\n\\n**Note:** The documentation excerpt doesn't detail the internal plugin API, session event schemas, or transcript format specifications—these implementation details aren't covered in the provided content.\",\"durationMs\":6948,\"url\":\"https://github.com/opencode-ai/opencode\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"b6d2dc9b-559d-43bb-8c0a-0e71f20007b4\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"5f00bc80-8df6-4e02-87fa-69c6bc2166b9\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"2d389bae-1365-4122-9ff2-46fd02f68c8d\",\"version\":\"2.1.37\",\"gitBranch\":\"feat/add-opencode\",\"slug\":\"graceful-booping-emerson\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_015sAyV6Mp159vc4Zp4SGSsH\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"# OpenCode Plugin System Overview\\n\\n## Plugin Architecture\\n\\nPlugins are JavaScript/TypeScript modules that extend OpenCode functionality. Each plugin exports a function receiving a context object and returning a hooks object.\\n\\n**Basic Structure:**\\n```javascript\\nexport const MyPlugin = async ({ project, client, $, directory, worktree }) => {\\n  return {\\n    // Hook implementations\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Context Parameters:**\\n- `project`: Current project information\\n- `client`: OpenCode SDK client for AI interaction\\n- `$`: Bun's shell API for command execution\\n- `directory`: Current working directory\\n- `worktree`: Git worktree path\\n\\n## Plugin Loading\\n\\n### Installation Methods\\n\\n1. **Local files**: Place in `.opencode/plugins/` (project) or `~/.config/opencode/plugins/` (global)\\n2. **npm packages**: Specify in config via `\\\"plugin\\\"` array\\n\\n### Load Order\\n1. Global config\\n2. Project config\\n3. Global plugin directory\\n4. Project plugin directory\\n\\nnpm packages auto-install via Bun to `~/.cache/opencode/node_modules/`.\\n\\n## Available Events\\n\\n**Command**: `command.executed`\\n\\n**File**: `file.edited`, `file.watcher.updated`\\n\\n**Installation**: `installation.updated`\\n\\n**LSP**: `lsp.client.diagnostics`, `lsp.updated`\\n\\n**Message**: `message.part.removed`, `message.part.updated`, `message.removed`, `message.updated`\\n\\n**Permission**: `permission.asked`, `permission.replied`\\n\\n**Server**: `server.connected`\\n\\n**Session**: `session.created`, `session.compacted`, `session.deleted`, `session.diff`, `session.error`, `session.idle`, `session.status`, `session.updated`\\n\\n**Todo**: `todo.updated`\\n\\n**Shell**: `shell.env`\\n\\n**Tool**: `tool.execute.after`, `tool.execute.before`\\n\\n**TUI**: `tui.prompt.append`, `tui.command.execute`, `tui.toast.show`\\n\\n## Key API Methods\\n\\n**Logging:**\\n```typescript\\nawait client.app.log({\\n  body: {\\n    service: \\\"plugin-name\\\",\\n    level: \\\"info|debug|warn|error\\\",\\n    message: \\\"text\\\",\\n    extra: {}\\n  }\\n})\\n```\\n\\n## Custom Tools\\n\\nPlugins can define tools using the `tool` helper:\\n\\n```typescript\\nimport { type Plugin, tool } from \\\"@opencode-ai/plugin\\\"\\n\\nexport const CustomToolsPlugin: Plugin = async (ctx) => {\\n  return {\\n    tool: {\\n      mytool: tool({\\n        description: \\\"Tool description\\\",\\n        args: { foo: tool.schema.string() },\\n        async execute(args, context) {\\n          return \\\"result\\\"\\n        }\\n      }