eding Entire to feed anything back. The transcript Entire captures is purely for its own purposes—checkpoint metadata, explain, summarize—so it doesn't actually need to live in a location that OpenCode can access.\\n\\nThe real constraint is timing: the plugin writes the transcript to disk, then calls the Go hook handler, which needs to read that transcript before it runs. So the transcript just needs to exist somewhere accessible on disk before the hook executes—even a temp file would work as long as the path gets passed in the hook payload. The flow is straightforward: plugin accumulates messages in memory, writes the transcript on `session.idle`, then triggers the hook with the transcript location.\\n\\nAfter the Go handler creates the checkpoint and copies it to the shadow branch, the transcript file becomes ephemeral—the actual data lives on git branches after condensation. So storing it in `.git/entire-sessions/opencode/` makes sense since that directory is already gitignored and managed by Entire, or a temp directory would be equally honest about its temporary nature.\\n\\nFor the resume question, OpenCode would just use its own SQLite database—Entire doesn't need to feed anything back. The `FormatResumeCommand` is just returning an informational command string for the user. Let me look at what `.git/entire-sessions/` currently contains.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":73,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":109758,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":73},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYHTpQjjbQkRz2TieeKfJ\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"13d12a05-11d2-4367-a104-e1aa09cf49a2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T12:55:48.730Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"13d12a05-11d2-4367-a104-e1aa09cf49a2\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/