andler can read it, within the same `turn-end` call.** After that, it gets copied to git refs and the file is disposable. So the options are:\\n\\n1. **`os.TempDir()`** — most honest (it IS ephemeral). PR #341 did this.\\n2. **`.git/entire-sessions/transcripts/`** — keeps everything in the repo, under Entire's existing namespace. No squatting on `~/.opencode/`.\\n3. **`.entire/opencode/`** — in the repo working tree, already gitignored.\\n\\nAnd no, you would NOT need to \\\"feed data back into SQLite\\\" for resume. OpenCode manages its own sessions via its own SQLite. `FormatResumeCommand(\\\"opencode --session <id>\\\")` would tell OpenCode to resume from its own storage. Entire's transcript copy is for Entire's purposes only (checkpoint metadata, explain, summarize) — it's a one-way read.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":271,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":121484,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":271},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYHTuWSvHpgo4wFBcyFzV\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"e00a6d1a-4aa3-44bf-b4c7-51e891a7295f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T12:56:50.027Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e00a6d1a-4aa3-44bf-b4c7-51e891a7295f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"2d389bae-1365-4122-9ff2-46fd02f68c8d\",\"version\":\"2.1.37\",\"gitBranch\":\"feat/add-opencode\",\"slug\":\"graceful-booping-emerson\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"ecb69617-a527-4715-a6cc-3ccfa3f16cf2\",\"toolUseID\":\"ecb69617-a527-4715-a6cc-3ccfa3f16cf2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T12:56:50.062Z\",\"uuid\":\"6f74329e-5a3f-451d-97d9-41fbedb4232e\"}\n